2 SENATE BILL 402
1 (II) FOR A VIOLATION RECORDED BY A SPEED MONITORING
2 SYSTEM LOCATED IN BALTIMORE CITY, A CIVIL PENALTY UNDER THIS SUBSECTION
3 MAY NOT EXCEED $60.
4 (3) For purposes of this section, the District Court shall prescribe:
5 (i) A uniform citation form consistent with subsection (d)(1) of this
6 section and § 7–302 of the Courts Article; and
7 (ii) A civil penalty, which shall be indicated on the citation, to be paid
8 by persons who choose to prepay the civil penalty without appearing in District Court.
9 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
10 October 1, 2025.

